This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D convolutional neural networks applied in video or 3D point cloud recognition. It may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it discusses neural network compression. Additionally, it could be categorized under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with deep learning models. The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with video recognition.
